"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893075","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-08","<p>Data on adults who are obese are published by obesity prevalence rather than the number of adults who are obese.</p><p> </p><p>Health Survey for England records adult obesity prevalence figures for England and the London region on an annual basis. Data from 2010 to 2016 are available to view here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/health-survey-for-england" target="_blank">https://digital.nhs.uk/data-and-information/publications/statistical/health-survey-for-england</a></p><p> </p><p>The Public Health Outcomes Framework provides estimates of obesity prevalence in adults aged 18 and over at local authority level, including London boroughs for 2015/16 to 2016/17 which is available to view here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://fingertips.phe.org.uk/profile/public-health-outcomes-framework/supporting-information/further-info" target="_blank">https://fingertips.phe.org.uk/profile/public-health-outcomes-framework/supporting-information/further-info</a></p><p> </p><p>Data from before 2015/16 are based on a different method of calculating this indicator, therefore are not comparable to the more recent years.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-08T16:06:21.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893075/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893075/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-27","Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many adults were recorded as obese in (a) England, (b) London, (c) each primary care trust in London and (d) each London borough in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","138979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893076","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-08","<p>We are delivering the most ambitious childhood obesity plan in the world. Key measures include the soft drinks industry levy, helping children to exercise more, funding more research and cutting sugar and calories in food. We are already seeing results with many in the food and drinks industry reducing levels of sugar in their products. This will impact on tackling obesity across all age groups.</p><p> </p><p>All reports and data published on progress in delivering our plan will be open to scrutiny. We will use this to determine whether sufficient progress has been made and whether alternative levers need to be considered.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-05-08T16:00:24.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893076/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/893076/answer",,,,,,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-27","Obesity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what steps the Government is taking to reduce levels of obesity.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","138980"
