"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892177","Home Office","false","2018-04-30","<p>The Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse published its Interim Report on 25 April. The Report contains a series of recommendations for specific changes, several of which are directed at Government. The Government welcomes the Report and is now considering the Inquiry’s recommendations very carefully. We will respond fully in due course.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","138469 ; 138470 ; 138471","2018-04-30T15:17:15.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892177/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892177/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-26","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will bring forward proposals to establish (a) levels of public expenditure and (b) measures to assess the effectiveness of that expenditure on services provided by her Department for child victims and adult survivors of child sexual abuse in line with the recommendation of the Interim Report of the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse, published on 25 April 2018.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","138472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892178","Department for Education","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse published its Interim Report on 25 April. The Report contains a series of recommendations for specific changes, several of which are directed at government. The government welcomes the Report and is now considering the Inquiry’s recommendations very carefully. We will respond fully in due course.</p><p> </p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi",,"2018-05-03T16:10:10.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892178/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892178/answer",,,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-26","Offences against Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if he will bring forward proposals to establish (a) levels of public expenditure and (b) measures to assess the effectiveness of that expenditure on services provided by his Department for child victims and adult survivors of child sexual abuse in line with the recommendation of the Interim Report of the Independent Inquiry into Child Sexual Abuse, published on 25 April 2018.","false","Biography information for Sarah Champion","Rotherham","Sarah Champion","138473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892179","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Government is considering all factors in relation to the UK’s future participation, or otherwise, in the EU ETS, in consultation with stakeholders.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-05-03T15:32:41.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892179/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892179/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-26","EU Emissions Trading Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether it is the Government’s policy to seek to stay within the European Emissions Trading Scheme after the scheme’s third trading phase expires on 31 December 2020.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","138512"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892180","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>The agreement governing our future relationship with the EU can only be legally concluded once the UK has left the EU. Article 50 sets out that the Withdrawal Agreement should take account of the framework of the future relationship with the EU, so at the same time as we negotiate the Withdrawal Agreement, we will seek to articulate our ambition for a deep and special partnership with the EU. Whatever the nature of the future UK-EU relationship, the UK will remain committed to international efforts to tackle climate change and working closely with the EU on such global challenges will remain very important.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","138514","2018-05-09T16:33:10.663Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892180/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892180/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-26","Energy and Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether his Department has plans to negotiate the inclusion of text on climate and energy in the political declaration on the framework for the future relationship that will form part of the European Commission's Draft Agreement on the withdrawal of the UK from the EU.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","138513"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892181","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>The agreement governing our future relationship with the EU can only be legally concluded once the UK has left the EU. Article 50 sets out that the Withdrawal Agreement should take account of the framework of the future relationship with the EU, so at the same time as we negotiate the Withdrawal Agreement, we will seek to articulate our ambition for a deep and special partnership with the EU. Whatever the nature of the future UK-EU relationship, the UK will remain committed to international efforts to tackle climate change and working closely with the EU on such global challenges will remain very important.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","138513","2018-05-09T16:33:10.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892181/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892181/answer",,,,,,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-26","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that there is continued cooperation with the EU on climate change after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Matthew Pennycook","Greenwich and Woolwich","Matthew Pennycook","138514"
