"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892184","Home Office","false","2018-05-01","<p>The Home Office publishes a list of Border, Immigration and Citizenship application fees and estimated unit costs. The unit cost for an application for indefinite leave to remain is detailed on page 5 of the following linked table.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/691200/Fees_Unit_Cost_Table_-_April_2018.pdf" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/691200/Fees_Unit_Cost_Table_-_April_2018.pdf</a></p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2018-05-01T10:21:59.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892184/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892184/answer",,,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-26","Immigration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what is the cost to the public purse is of processing an application for indefinite leave to remain.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","138521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892185","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-08","<p>Between April and December 2017 prison officers attended hospital for treatment following 741 incidents of assault. This information was not recorded for incidents that occurred before April 2017, and data for the first three months of 2018 is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p>These figures have been drawn from the HMPPS Incident Reporting System, and while care is taken when processing and analysing returns, the detail is subject to the inaccuracies inherent in any large-scale recording system.</p><p> </p><p>We are taking urgent action to make prisons safer, and assaults on our hardworking staff will never be tolerated. We are ensuring that prison officers have the tools they need to do their jobs by rolling out body worn cameras, 'police-style' handcuffs and restraints, and trialling PAVA incapacitant spray.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","138497","2018-05-08T16:37:04.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892185/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892185/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-26","Prison Officers: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers required hospital treatment as a result of an assault at work in 2017.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","138496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892186","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-08","<p>Between April and December 2017 prison officers attended hospital for treatment following 741 incidents of assault. This information was not recorded for incidents that occurred before April 2017, and data for the first three months of 2018 is not yet available.</p><p> </p><p>These figures have been drawn from the HMPPS Incident Reporting System, and while care is taken when processing and analysing returns, the detail is subject to the inaccuracies inherent in any large-scale recording system.</p><p> </p><p>We are taking urgent action to make prisons safer, and assaults on our hardworking staff will never be tolerated. We are ensuring that prison officers have the tools they need to do their jobs by rolling out body worn cameras, 'police-style' handcuffs and restraints, and trialling PAVA incapacitant spray.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","138496","2018-05-08T16:37:04.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892186/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892186/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-26","Prison Officers: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers required hospital treatment as a result of an assault at work in the first three months of 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","138497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892187","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-01","<p>The latest available prison performance ratings data cover the period 2016/17 and are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-annual-performance-ratings-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-annual-performance-ratings-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>40 prisons were rated as having overall performance of concern in 2016/17. There were 62 prison officers from these prisons working on Detached Duty at other public-sector prisons during January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>There were 16 prison officers from prisons in special measures working on Detached Duty at other public-sector prisons during January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Detached Duty is one of the sensible and proportionate measures we take to ensure we run safe and decent regimes in prisons and respond appropriately to any operational issues that arise.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","138499","2018-05-01T16:42:35.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892187/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892187/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-26","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers that work at prisons rated as Overall performance is of concern were working on detached duty at another prison during January 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","138498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892188","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-01","<p>The latest available prison performance ratings data cover the period 2016/17 and are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-annual-performance-ratings-2016-to-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/prison-annual-performance-ratings-2016-to-2017</a>.</p><p>40 prisons were rated as having overall performance of concern in 2016/17. There were 62 prison officers from these prisons working on Detached Duty at other public-sector prisons during January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>There were 16 prison officers from prisons in special measures working on Detached Duty at other public-sector prisons during January 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Detached Duty is one of the sensible and proportionate measures we take to ensure we run safe and decent regimes in prisons and respond appropriately to any operational issues that arise.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","138498","2018-05-01T16:42:35.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892188/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892188/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-26","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers who work at prisons which are in special measures were working on detached duty at another prison during January 2018.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","138499"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892189","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-04","<p>Since 2010, following consultation, 24 courts have closed and the leases of the buildings were not renewed or extended. Since 2015, 1 tribunal has closed and the lease of the building was not renewed or extended. In the case of tribunals, HM Courts and Tribunals Service does not hold information centrally for closures pre-dating 2015.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2018-05-04T13:31:36.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892189/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/892189/answer",,,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-26","Courts and Tribunals: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many (a) courts and (b) tribunals have closed as a result of leases not being extended in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","138500"
