"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891341","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2018-05-01","<p>Political dialogue under the auspices of the Economic Community of West African States, and mediated by the President of Ghana, is ongoing. We support this regionally led effort to broker a path towards elections in Togo. The mediators have recommended that all parties refrain from protest while the dialogue continues. We encourage both Government and the opposition parties to continue with the dialogue process to reach an agreed political solution, and urge all parties to avoid violence.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson","138001 ; 138002 ; 138003","2018-05-01T15:33:08.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891341/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891341/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/891341/answer",,,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2018-04-25","Togo: Demonstrations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations he has made to his counterpart in Togo on reports of the use of excessive force against people participating in peaceful demonstrations in that country.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","138000"
